programme.desc: Based on the inspiring story of Solomon Northup, a free African-American from upstate New York who was sold into slavery in 1841, as he endures the most terrible kinds of torture and humiliation in his journey of survival and freedom.

programme.title: Lady Macbeth
programme.desc: Adapted from Nikolai Leskov's Lady Macbeth of the Mtsensk District, the movie depicts the life of a young woman stifled by her marriage of convenience to a man twice her age. Confined and left behind by her husband, she starts a romance with a young man from the estate.

programme.title: K-19: The Widowmaker
programme.desc: During its maiden voyage in the North Atlantic in 1961, Russia's first nuclear submarine malfunctions, and it's up to Captain Alexei Vostrikov and Officer Mikhail Polenin to save the ship and prevent a nuclear disaster.

programme.title: Hart's War
programme.desc: When Lieutenant Thomas Hart is transferred to a German POW camp, he gets dragged into the daring scheme of Colonel William McNamara, who is using a sham trial to cover his plans to escape and destroy a nearby munitions plant.

programme.title: The Perfect Catch
programme.desc: A struggling single mother fights to keep her small-town diner afloat. Brought down by a series of disappointments and abandonments, she finds a sliver of hope in the form of an old boyfriend, Chase, who is a professional baseball player who comes to his childhood home after a career disappointment.

programme.title: Henry's Crime
programme.desc: An innocent highway tollbooth worker is convicted of a bank heist, and decides to take the fall for a crime he did not do. While in jail, his formerly pathless life is altered when he meets his cellmate Max, a con man with whom he plans to rob a bank upon his release.

programme.title: Top Gun
programme.desc: The Naval Fighter Weapons School witnesses a fierce competition between two students, nicknamed Maverick and Iceman, as they try to win the school's top trophy.

programme.title: The Pink Panther
programme.desc: After a famous soccer player was killed during a match , and his ring known as the Pink Panther gets stolen, the chief of investigations (Dreyfus) appoints the worst police inspector (Clouseau) for the case, while he uses his best men to hunt down the murderer and thief.

programme.title: The Pink Panther 2
programme.desc: Inspector Jacques Clouseau (Steve Martin) returns after solving the mystery of the Pink Panther Diamond, his angry boss Dreyfus tries to keep him in minor cases, but the rare diamond is stolen again with other artifacts around the world. A team of the greatest detectives is formed to retrieve these things and Clouseau is among them.

programme.title: Green Book
programme.desc: In 1962, Tony "Tony Lip” (Viggo Mortensen), an Italian-American tough bouncer, is hired to be the driver for the African-American classical pianist Dr. Don Shirley (Mahershala Ali) for a concert tour into the Deep South states. Because of America's racial segregation, Shirley relies on The Negro Motorist Green Book to guide them to small hotels, restaurants and gas stations. As the disparate pair witness and endure America's appalling injustices on the road, they find a newfound respect for each that opens their eyes to the world around them.

programme.title: Dark Waters
programme.desc: The true story of how one man stood up against a major corporation after the latter is connected to a number of deaths. Filing a lawsuit against the company, he faces a tremendous amount of pressure as he tries to put a stop to their practices that pollute the environment.

programme.title: Hell or High Water
programme.desc: A divorced father and his ex-con brother start a series of bank robberies to keep their family's ranch in West Texas, while two Texas Rangers try to catch them.

programme.title: Gone Girl
programme.desc: On the occasion of his fifth wedding anniversary, Nick Dunne reports that his wife, Amy, has gone missing. Under pressure from the police and a growing media frenzy, Nick's portrait of a blissful union begins to crumble. Soon his lies, deceits and strange behavior have everyone asking the same dark question: Did Nick Dunne kill his wife.

programme.title: Eastern Promises
programme.desc: In a London hospital, a Russian teenager dies while giving birth, and the midwife finds her diary that contains clues leading to a Russian mob family that has assaulted her.

programme.title: Bad Lieutenant: Port of Call New Orleans
programme.desc: Terence McDonagh is a troubled detective who gets addicted to painkillers following an injury during Hurricane Katrina. As he's having trouble dealing with people in his life, he has to get his act together in order to help solve a series of murders.

programme.title: Dreamgirls
programme.desc: As Curtis tries to make it as a music manager, he provides a career change for a girls' band that consists of three soul singers. But as he tries to make the band into headliner material, he ends up demoting then firing the lead singer to replace her with another whom he deems more fit for stardom.

programme.title: Chicago
programme.desc: (Roxie Hart ) and (Velma Kelly) each commit a murder; Roxie killed her boyfriend , and Velma killed her husband and sister. The two women grab the attention of the Chicago media,that love scandals. They both share the same lawyer (Billy Flynn) who tries to acquit them of their charges.

programme.title: De-Lovely
programme.desc: A biography of Cole Carter, his musical works and his unusual relationship with his wife.

programme.title: Inception
programme.desc: Armed with a technology that enables him to enter people's dreams and get access to their subconscious, Dom is hired to carry out a complicated task: set up the perfect circumstances to plant an idea in the mind of a businessman in the dream world.(n)

programme.title: House at the End of the Street
programme.desc: After her parents separate, Elissa moves with her mother to their dream house in the country. But the dream is disturbed when they learn that the house at the end of their street was the scene of a violent crime where a girl killed her parents.(n)

programme.title: Misery
programme.desc: When the famous novelist Paul Sheldon has an accident, his life spirals out of control. Nurse Annie Wilkes takes him to her remote house, but Sheldon gradually discovers that she is an obsessed fan of his works, and she is only torturing him slowly to get him to write her stories.(n)

programme.title: The Man in the Iron Mask
programme.desc: As the anger against King Louis XIV reaches boiling point, the three Musketeers unite with D'Artagnan to replace the hated king with his secret twin brother who has been imprisoned and put in an iron mask to hide his true identity.(n)

programme.desc: During the Cold War era between the US and the former Soviet Union, the true story of the legendary American chess player Bobby Fischer (Toby Maguire), and the circumstances of his confrontation with his Russian counterpart Boris Spassky (Liev Schreiber) in a high level game of chess.(n)

programme.title: Spontaneous
